      <akn:section eId="sec_38_824_02">
        <akn:num>38-824.02</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Physical and health education requirements.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-824_02_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Public schools and public charter schools shall provide physical education as follows:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-824_02_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Public schools and public charter schools shall provide health education to students in Grades Kindergarten through 8 as follows:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-824_02_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The State Board of Education, with assistance from the Office of the State Superintendent of Education, shall consider ways to expand physical education in high schools.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-824_02_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The physical education and health education required by this section shall meet the curricular standards adopted by the State Board of Education.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
